entry.et: Middle English westerne, from Old English; akin to Old High German westrōni western, Old English west

def.dt: :coming from the west a western storm
:of, relating to, or characteristic of a region conventionally designated West: as
:steeped in or stemming from the Greco-Roman traditions Western culture
:of or relating to the noncommunist countries of Europe and America
:of or relating to the American West Western clothes
:of or relating to the Roman Catholic or Protestant segment of Christianity Western liturgies
:one that is produced in or characteristic of a western region and especially the western United States
:a novel, story, motion picture, or broadcast dealing with life in the western United States especially during the latter half of the 19th century
:a blot consisting of a sheet of nitrocellulose or nylon that contains spots of protein for identification by a suitable molecular probe and is used especially for the detection of antibodies
:the half of the earth comprising North and South America and surrounding waters
:an omelet made usually with diced ham, green pepper, and onion called also Denver omelet
:a large arborvitae (Thuja plicata) chiefly of the Pacific Northwest with reddish-brown bark and wood called also red cedar
:the wood of the western red cedar
:a deep-seated saddle used originally by cattlemen that has broad skirts and fenders and a high pommel with a horn for holding the lariat called also stock saddle
:a sandwich filled with a western omelet called also Denver sandwich
:swing music played typically on country-music instruments (as guitar, fiddle, or steel guitar)
state W Australia on Indian Ocean ✽ Perth area 975,920 square miles (2,537,392 square kilometers), pop 1,676,400
